trend_summary: From earliest to latest scenes, suburban settlement intensifies: residential infill thickens, northern industrial strip grows, and new institutional buildings occupy former farmland. Road network and parking coverage expand while tree and crop cover shrink. A quarry enlarges south-central, highlighting ongoing land conversion. Overall built fabric remains patchy amid vegetation, indicating medium-density suburban growth.
notable_changes: Residential infill and cul-de-sacs densify northern neighbourhoods, reducing tree canopy.
Expansion of light-industrial/warehouse blocks along the northern edge replaces woodland.
Large institutional or logistics complex erected in east-central farmland between mid and late images.
South-central quarry/extractive site widens, with new pits and spoil piles visible.
Farmland in the northeast transitions to mixed development and sports/parking surfaces.
